Definition: epilepsy characterized clinically by impairment of consciousness and amnesia for the episode
Example: often involves purposeful movements of the arms and legs and sometimes hallucinations
Synonyms: temporal_lobe_epilepsy, epilepsy, characterized, clinically, by, impairment, of, consciousness, and, amnesia, for, the, episode, often, involves, purposeful, movements, arms, legs, sometimes, hallucinations
Category: noun.state
